    "body": "Hey @hawkofsky, I tried to reproduce this but I couldn't. Here's what I tried.\r\n\r\nI have this solidity code:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/proxy/ClonesUpgradeable.sol\";\r\n\r\nimport \"hardhat/console.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract Foo {}\r\n\r\ncontract Test {\r\n  function createClone(address implementation) public {\r\n    address clone = ClonesUpgradeable.clone(implementation);\r\n    console.log(clone);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nand this test:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst { expect } = require(\"chai\");\r\n\r\ndescribe(\"clones\", function () {\r\n  it(\"test\", async function () {\r\n    const foo = await ethers.deployContract(\"Foo\");\r\n    const test = await ethers.deployContract(\"Test\");\r\n\r\n    await test.createClone(foo.target);\r\n  });\r\n\r\n  it(\"test 2\", async function () {\r\n    const foo = await ethers.deployContract(\"Foo\");\r\n    const test = await ethers.deployContract(\"Test\");\r\n\r\n    await test.createClone(foo.target);\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd two different addresses are logged.\r\n\r\nOne reason why this could be happening to you is if you are resetting the network, for example doing something like:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  // reset the network before each test\r\n  beforeEach(async function () {\r\n    await network.provider.send(\"hardhat_reset\", [])\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe other reason this could be happening is if you are using [fixtures](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/guides/test-contracts#using-fixtures), which use snapshots under the hood.\r\n\r\nIf neither of those is the case, then we'll need a [minimal reproducible example](https://stackoverflow.com/help/minimal-reproducible-example) to be able to look into this.",
